t":""}],"posts":[{"title":"恭喜自己，好不容易遇到你","slug":"01-博客诞生","date":"2022-04-20T13:00:00.000Z","updated":"2022-04-21T14:23:03.477Z","comments":true,"path":"posts/1.html","link":"","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/posts/1.html","excerpt":"","text":"进步一点点 为什么建博客？就是玩 展望博客整理一些前端知识、优秀的设计作品或生活方面有兴趣的事发到博客上供大家交流 关于博主憨批一个","categories":[{"name":"生活","slug":"生活","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/categories/%E7%94%9F%E6%B4%BB/"}],"tags":[{"name":"想法","slug":"想法","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/tags/%E6%83%B3%E6%B3%95/"}]},{"title":"Alpha Design","slug":"02-博客诞生","date":"2022-04-20T13:00:00.000Z","updated":"2022-04-21T14:47:05.615Z","comments":true,"path":"posts/2.html","link":"","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/posts/2.html","excerpt":"","text":"进步一点点 Alpha Design原研哉，平面设计师，日本设计中心代表取缔役社长，武藏野美术大学教授，日本平面设计协会副会长。 Sample Recommend 溜溜球啦！","categories":[{"name":"设计","slug":"设计","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/categories/%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1/"}],"tags":[{"name":"想法","slug":"想法","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/tags/%E6%83%B3%E6%B3%95/"}]},{"title":"Wait a moment 究竟要别人等多久？","slug":"03-博客诞生","date":"2021-05-27T13:00:00.000Z","updated":"2022-04-21T15:08:38.245Z","comments":true,"path":"posts/9560087c.html","link":"","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/posts/9560087c.html","excerpt":"","text":"进步一点点 01. A moment究竟是多久？ Wait a moment是一个很常用的句子，需要注意的是，a moment其实很快，如果你需要别人等较久的时间，要用a while。 不过，如果直接说wait a while，听起来就有点harsh（刺耳；严厉）。你可以加上其他词来软化它: You might have to wait a while. 你可能得等一会儿。 这里加上might就显得更委婉、客气。 当你去网红餐厅排队等位的时候，服务员可能告诉你： I’m afraid it might take a while. 恐怕要等一段时间。 国外有些餐厅会在等位区摆一张桌子，你可以坐在那张桌子旁边但是不能点菜吃。 It is a waiting table. 这是等待台。 Wait还可以作名词： It might be a long wait. 可能要等很长一段时间。 02. Drop the “wait” 其实，英语国家的人很少直接用wait，即使要用，也会用非常礼貌的语言来修饰它。现在我们就来讲一些不带wait却能表示“等一会”的说法。 Just a moment. 就一小会。 这种表达把wait a moment里的wait去掉了，听起来更有礼貌。 更口语的说法——hold on。 Can you hold on for one second? 你能稍等一小会吗？ 告诉别人等一会，不要那么猴急，中文说“猴”，英文说“马”： Hold your horses. “勒住你的马”，也就是说稍安勿躁，慢慢来。 Hang on也是一种非正式的表达。 Hang on. We gotta fix this. 稍等一下，我们得解决这个问题。 “给我一些时间”可以说： Give me a minute/second. 还有一种非常礼貌的用语： Please bear with me. 请原谅我，请忍一忍。 这里的bear可不是熊。Bear作动词表示“忍受”。Bear with me意思也就是give me a break / go easy on me.（请稍候，忍我一下） 03. “等等我”不是wait me 中国人常常把“等等我”说成wait me，这其实是错误的。“等着我”英语是： Wait for me. Wait for不仅可以用于等人，还可以用于等车：wait for the bus/train。 I’m waiting to get on the plane. I’m waiting at the airport. Wait for a table. 等座位 英语里面还有一种说法是wait（on）tables，这里的wait可不是等位，而是指餐厅服务员的工作——to work as a waiter。","categories":[{"name":"生活","slug":"生活","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/categories/%E7%94%9F%E6%B4%BB/"}],"tags":[{"name":"想法","slug":"想法","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/tags/%E6%83%B3%E6%B3%95/"}]}],"categories":[{"name":"生活","slug":"生活","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/categories/%E7%94%9F%E6%B4%BB/"},{"name":"设计","slug":"设计","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/categories/%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1/"}],"tags":[{"name":"想法","slug":"想法","permalink":"https://github.com/morandi484/morandi484.github.io.git/tags/%E6%83%B3%E6%B3%95/"}]}